# SoftDent data pull (universal — ALL reports)

Whenever SoftDent desktop is used to pull financial or report data — **every** SoftDent report (aging, register, collections, daysheet, transactions, claims, writeoff, insurance income, production, or any other SoftDent Output Options dialog):

## Allowed Output Options only

1. **Excel** — select Excel → Enter → complete SoftDent Setup / save flow. Prefer for money beams and morning bundle. SoftDent Select File Name → `C:\SoftDentReportExports` for **all** Excel reports.
2. **Print Preview** — select Print Preview → Enter → read the **last page** for totals when Excel is unavailable.

## Forbidden (no report is exempt)

- **Never Printer** — SoftDent often defaults to Printer; do not leave it selected and do not OK a print job. If SoftDent waits on a printer dialog, Cancel (`Alt+C`).
- **Never File** — do not use SoftDent “File”; Select File Name must stay under `C:\SoftDentReportExports` (never OneDrive / `C:\SoftDent\softdentexportreports`).
- **Never invent dollars** — empty export ≠ `$0` (`emptyNotZero`).
- **Never SoftDent write-back** — read-only pulls only.

## Defaults

- Launch SoftDent only via **CS SoftDent Software.lnk** (`-sus`), never bare `SDWIN.EXE`.
- Sign On: prefer `SOFTDENT_SIGNON_*` / `SOFTDENT_GUI_*` when set; else **`COMPUTE`** / **`computer`** (lowercase, case-sensitive).
- SoftDent UI: keyboard or mouse only. **Never Esc** on SoftDent main (quit prompt).
- Next-business-day money reports: pull at **9:00 PM local the night before**.

## Agents / automation

- GUI export code and HAL playbooks must enforce Excel | Print Preview only for **every** catalog report (`neverUsePrinter` / `neverUseFile`).
- If Excel is greyed: Print Preview only — do not fall through to Printer or File.
- After Excel save, SoftDent may open a temp workbook — SaveCopyAs into `C:\SoftDentReportExports`. Select File Name for every Excel report is `C:\SoftDentReportExports`.
